<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Common Mistakes When Choosing Hoops</h2>

  <ul class="plainList">
    <li><strong>Choosing hoops that are too low:</strong> limits plant growth and airflow.</li>
    <li><strong>Ignoring bed width:</strong> leads to unstable setups.</li>
    <li><strong>Using too few hoops:</strong> causes sagging and uneven coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Not anchoring properly:</strong> reduces effectiveness in wind.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The best hoop system is one that fits the bed and stays stable under real conditions.
  </p>
</section>

